<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="427" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 322.112J72/11.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 24.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Guayaquil</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-13">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 13, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that Mr.
                            Robert B. Jones, the American citizen who was illegally imprisoned, was
                            discharged March 11, 1914, at noon, under an opinion given by the judge
                            a copy of which is enclosed.<note n="8" xml:id="d427fn8">Not
                                printed.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>As stated by the judge, not a suspicion was ever against him, yet he, an
                            innocent man was compelled to pass three months in a filthy jail
                            associated with the vilest criminals, the neglect of his business having
                            been the cause of his financial ruin, as well as the loss of health of
                            his wife.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Frederic W. Goding</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>